Fix AOT warnings in `/tmp/sv-9917669f2a734322a169b431156e3b0d/before/Common/Custom/Models/ManagedServiceIdentity.Serialization.cs`. Do NOT modify any files in the `after/` directory.

This file has 4 `JsonSerializer` calls that produce IL2026/IL3050 warnings. Replace each one:

**Line 31:** `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, ManagedServiceIdentityType, jOptions);`
This uses a custom `JsonConverter<ManagedServiceIdentityType>` whose `Write` method does:
```csharp
writer.WritePropertyName("type");
writer.WriteStringValue(model.ToString());
```
Replace the `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, ManagedServiceIdentityType, jOptions);` call with inline equivalent:
```csharp
writer.WritePropertyName("type"u8);
writer.WriteStringValue(ManagedServiceIdentityType.ToString());
```

**Line 49:** `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, item.Value, jOptions);`
`item.Value` is a `UserAssignedIdentity` which implements `IJsonModel<UserAssignedIdentity>`. Replace with:
```csharp
writer.WriteObjectValue(item.Value, options);
```
(where `options` is the `ModelReaderWriterOptions` parameter of the enclosing `Write` method)

**Line 206:** `type = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<ManagedServiceIdentityType>($"{{{property}}}");`
The converter's `Read` method parses `{"type":"value"}` and extracts the value. The simpler/AOT-safe replacement is:
```csharp
if (property.Value.ValueKind == JsonValueKind.Null)
{
    type = default;
}
else
{
    type = new ManagedServiceIdentityType(property.Value.GetString());
}
```

**Line 218:** `dictionary.Add(new ResourceIdentifier(property0.Name), JsonSerializer.Deserialize<UserAssignedIdentity>(property0.Value.GetRawText()));`
`UserAssignedIdentity` has a static `DeserializeUserAssignedIdentity(JsonElement)` method. Replace with:
```csharp
dictionary.Add(new ResourceIdentifier(property0.Name), UserAssignedIdentity.DeserializeUserAssignedIdentity(property0.Value));
```

Use the `edit` tool for all changes. After making changes, verify with:
```bash
cd /tmp/sv-9917669f2a734322a169b431156e3b0d/before && dotnet build --no-incremental 2>&1 | grep 'ManagedServiceIdentity.Serialization' | head -10
```

